<HEADLINE>
FT  14 NOV 92 / Milk marketing deadline set
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT has set October 1 1994 as the deadline to end the UK's
principal milk marketing scheme, according to the Agriculture Bill published
yesterday.
The Milk Marketing Board for England and Wales, along with the three milk
marketing boards in Scotland, have until the end of next year to submit
schemes for disposing of their assets to successor bodies.
Proposals to turn the MMB for England and Wales into a single voluntary
co-operative have run into opposition from the dairy trade.
</TEXT>
