   ABOUT 1,000 British Airways ground staff at Gatwick Airport
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
London, are to ballot on industrial action after the proposed introduction
of pay cuts averaging 25 per cent.
The ballot follows BA's takeover of Dan-Air and affects 1,250 BA ground
staff and short-haul cabin crew as part of cost cutting restructuring of
BA's Gatwick's services. The cut will not affect 450 former Dan-Air staff.
