<HEADLINE>
FT  14 NOV 92 / Citizen's Charter budget doubled
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government is to more than double the budget of the Citizen's Charter
unit, the Cabinet Office section responsible for raising the quality of
government services.
The unit's budget will rise from Pounds 3.7m this year to Pounds 8.5m next
year.
The unit announced yesterday it will pilot a Charterline telephone helpline
giving information on public services and how to complain when things go
wrong.
The pilot will be launched in the new year, with Price Waterhouse management
consultants as project managers.
</TEXT>
