(USDollars 136.5m) or CDollars 1.87 a share in the first nine months. This
compares with CDollars 129m or CDollars 1.43 a year earlier.
Consolidated revenues were little changed at CDollars 4.2bn,
The Great-West Lifeco made an increased contribution, as did Investors
Group. Pargesa, the European holding company jointly owned with the Frere
Group of Belgium, contributed CDollars 26.3m to Power Financial's earnings.
The latest period included a CDollars 61.5m special gain taken in the second
quarter, resulting from a stock issue by Investors Group.
Third-quarter profit was CDollars 28m or 31 cents a share, against CDollars
37m or 41 cents a year earlier on revenues of CDollars 1.39bn, little
changed.
United Westburne, the North American plumbing, heating and electrical goods
wholesaler controlled by Dumez of France, suffered a third-quarter loss of
CDollars 330,000 or 1 cent a share, against a profit of CDollars 2.7m or 7
cents.
Sales were CDollars 579m, down nearly 4 per cent, due to the sale of the
Memphis division.
The nine-month loss was CDollars 7.9m or 21 cents, including a Dollars 2m
loss from discontinued operations, against a loss of CDollars 4m or 11
cents. Sales for the period were little changed at CDollars 1.6bn.
