coast stations, reported a profit of ADollars 28m before interest and tax,
representing a gross return of 11 per cent on sales.
Mr Gary Rice, managing director, said the result was achieved in spite of
difficult trading conditions caused by slow economic growth.
He said he was confident the network could maintain its improved performance
in the current year.
