   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
On Sunday morning huge cranes will rumble through the Somerset village of
Street to remove one of its most famous landmarks. C&amp;J Clark, Britain's
biggest shoe maker, is selling the giant Henry Moore sculpture which graces
the lawns of its headquarters, writes Peggy Hollinger.
